public int countGoodSubstrings(String s) {
    int count = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < s.length() - 2; i++) {
        if (s.charAt(i) != s.charAt(i + 1) && s.charAt(i) != s.charAt(i + 2) && s.charAt(i + 1) != s.charAt(i + 2))
            count++;
    }
    return count;
}
```

    The algorithm iterates through the given string `s` till the third last character. For each character, it checks if the current character and the next two characters are distinct. If they are distinct, it means we have found a good substring of length three and increase the `count`. After the iteration, the function returns the total count of good substrings found.
